                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"183 is a factor of 2013. Moreover, N is exactly divisible by 2013. It follows that 183 completely divides  N leaving no remainder. Now, 183 is a smaller number compared to 2013. Thus, it is clear that 183 can be added a number of times in order to get closest to 1234(since 183 leaves a remainder when it divides 1234.) Now, 183 when added upon it six times, it gets summed up to 1098 and after that it exceeds if we try to add another 183 over the sum. Thus 1098 is the closest number to 1234 which is divisible by 183. Hence the difference(i.e. 136) is the remainder."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



